      'THE 2016 RUSSIAN INTRUSIONS: The Senate Intelligence Committee\'s bipartisan investigation confirmed that Russian military intelligence (GRU) targeted election infrastructure in all 50 states during the 2016 election cycle. The GRU successfully penetrated the Illinois State Board of Elections voter registration database, accessing records of up to 200,000 voters and extracting an unknown quantity of data. Arizona\'s registration system was also compromised. The Mueller Report documented that GRU officers sent spearphishing emails to over 120 local election officials and vendors. While the intelligence community assessed that no votes were changed, the full extent of the intrusions was never publicly disclosed; much of the evidence remains classified.',
      'DEEP ROOT ANALYTICS EXPOSURE: In June 2017, security researcher Chris Vickery discovered that Deep Root Analytics, a data firm contracted by the Republican National Committee, had left a database containing personal information on 198 million American voters exposed on an Amazon S3 server without password protection. The 1.1 terabyte database included names, dates of birth, home addresses, phone numbers, and modeled political preferences for virtually every registered voter in the United States. The data had been accessible to anyone with the URL for approximately two weeks. Deep Root Analytics faced no regulatory penalties; the incident highlighted the complete absence of federal data protection standards for voter information.',
